As written, I think the sauce is a bit tart and salty. It's not horrible, just not ...sublime... I have a problem with authority, so I used a bottle of zinfandel and regular (non-low sodium) broth. The reduction was quite tart, so I added a full cup of dried figs/cherries I had lying around, and stewed them in the broth. This was quite tasty. I finished it with a bunch of drippings and a bit extra butter, and it really was quite quite good. I had read a lot of reviews, and most were raves, but there was one woman who said, "sorry, people, but this sauce is too tart." I thought she was a sourpus, but in retrospect, I think that even with merlot, it would have been a little tart. I think it may be better with a port or something, and definitely use low sodium broth.

