Rating: 4
I made this for a fancy Father's Day dinner and it was excellent! Great food for a romantic dinner or celebration. I made the merlot and broth mixture the night before and then the rest of it when I was doing the steaks. Definitely stick to low-sodium because it is just enough salt;anymore would be too much. I also simmered my sauce for 30-40 minutes after bringing it to a final boil to get the syrup-like consistancy. The thicker the better. Which worked because it took 30 minutes to grill the steaks just right (as opposed to searing them). Next time I will do all of the sauce the night before in order to get it thicker. Excellent taste!

