Rating: 4
Delicious! This is a terrific recipe for a special dinner. The sauce is out of this world (be sure to follow the salt-free instructions, otherwise it is too salty). I also found that using the filet makes a tremendous difference, a lesser cut of meat just doesn't do the sauce justice. Because I wanted to prepare the meal a little ahead of time, I simply placed the sauteed meat in a glass serving dish with the sauce, covered, and put it in the oven on warm for an hour.

Rating: 4
Absolutely wonderful! I read the reviews prior to making this dish, so I had a concern about the salt, and used low sodium broth. I'm glad I did. I condensed the sauce first, then cooked a small pork shoulder roast with about 1/3 cup of the sauce in a cooking bag. After the roast was done I used a baster to remove the drippings from the bag, leaving the fat. I cooked the drippings down for about 5 minutes then added the sauce, heated through, then thickened. Oh My Word!! This is one of those hearty, full-flavored, yummy dishes. I served baked potatoes and used the sauce as a dressing. My husband raved.

